result.execSummary:
The defendant James D Willey was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Knowingly Violate a Domestic Abuse Order - Injunction, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 813.12(8)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: $265.60 fine/costs to be paid to the Clerk of Court Office within 60 days or set up payment plan. Bond to be applied to fine/costs.
$2,109.88 Restitution, plus 10% surcharge of $210.99, for a total of $2,320.87 to be paid to Probation while on Probation at an amount of $193.40 per month.
Must pay the $250.00 DNA surcharge to the COCC within 60 days or set up payment plan.  Failure to pay will be warrant. Bond to be applied to costs.
No contact with Donna Cotter or Gary Cotter.
Skidsteer to be returned to Donna Cotter.
